Preconditions:
- The input grid must not be null.
- The input grid must have at least one row and one column.
- The values in the grid must be within the range of 1 to 6.

Postconditions:
- The method should return true if there is a valid path from the upper-left cell to the bottom-right cell, following the streets.
- The method should return false if there is no valid path from the upper-left cell to the bottom-right cell, following the streets.